<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 2:11PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of northern Smyth,
Tazewell, and southwestern Bland Counties through 245 PM EDT...
At 210 PM EDT, strong thunderstorms extended along a line extending
from Jewell Ridge, to Claypool Hill, to near Allison Gap. Movement
was east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Marion...
Richlands...
Tazewell...
Saltville...
Cedar Bluff...
Ceres...
and Mount Rogers National Recreation Area.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Additional statements will be issued as conditions warrant.</instruction>
